topic of the PR is assigned to be the ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"K4q2DsrCej"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"shephard","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"VNEDYTB0hz"}],"key":"BqVW189UwZ"},{"type":"text","value":" of the RFC.\nThis simply means that their job is to ensure the conversation moves forward in a\ntransparent and inclusive manner. They are ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"tVPjvmmZ02"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"not","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"ib3fMagp6P"}],"key":"FLaDmaJLK0"},{"type":"text","value":" tasked with deciding or implementing the feature.","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"Fp8v8kqNtB"}],"key":"wsdrpUHges"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once the PR is made, the pull request enters an “open comments” period where people can\ndiscuss the proposal. Often this results in modifications to the PR as new ideas come up\nand old ideas get refined. Throughout this process, the shephard’s responsibility is to keep\nthings moving forward productively.","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"key":"UJEyc6mdjX"}],"key":"prx24y9uFN"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":134,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once a member of the sub-team (usually the shephard) believes that enough discussion has\nhappened, they call for a “final comments”\nperiod. This is their formal statement that “we’re ready to make a decision, so speak